// The demo program (inv-K-1 / inv-K-4 — K.W2).
//
// `demo/` only. Resolves the value.js library through the `@src/*` path and
// `@mkbabb/glass-ui` from SOURCE via the `development` export condition
// (`customConditions`), symmetric with the Vite `resolve.conditions` in
// `vite.config.ts` (`demoResolve`). Source-resolution is build-state
// INDEPENDENT (inv-K-4): the demo typecheck reads glass-ui's live `src/`, green
// whether glass-ui's `dist/` is fresh, stale, or deleted — which it provably is
// (glass-ui's dist `.d.ts` churns under its own active development; relying on
// it for TS is the coupling K removes).
//
// THE ERROR-SCOPING CONTRACT. Source-resolution pulls glass-ui's `src/` into
// this program, so vue-tsc also reports glass-ui's OWN internal diagnostics
// (~164 under value.js's stricter `exactOptionalPropertyTypes` /
// `noUncheckedIndexedAccess` floor, which glass-ui does not enforce on itself —
// a `.ts` dependency has no `.d.ts` trust boundary to skip-check). value.js's
// OWN demo code is type-clean against glass-ui source (0 `demo/` errors). The
// K.W2 gate (`scripts/check-types.mjs`, the `typecheck` script) therefore counts
// only value.js-OWNED errors (`src/` + `demo/`) and excludes `../glass-ui/`
// paths — glass-ui-source cleanliness under the strict floor is glass-ui's CI's
// responsibility, not value.js's, and is not per-file maskable here.
//
// This is the ONLY value.js program that may see glass-ui; the library program
// (tsconfig.lib.json) never does (inv-K-1 — structurally glass-ui-free).
{
    "extends": "./tsconfig.base.json",
    "compilerOptions": {
        "customConditions": ["development"],
        "paths": {
            "@src/*": ["./src/*"],
            "@styles/*": ["./demo/@/styles/*"],
            "@components/*": ["./demo/@/components/*"],
            "@utils/*": ["./demo/@/utils/*"],
            "@lib/*": ["./demo/@/lib/*"],
            "@composables/*": ["./demo/@/composables/*"],
            "@assets/*": ["./assets/*"],
            "vue": ["./node_modules/vue"],
            "@vue/*": ["./node_modules/@vue/*"],
            "@mkbabb/value.js": ["./src/index.ts"]
        }
    },
    // `src/vite-env.d.ts` carries `/// <reference types="vite/client" />`
    // (typing `import.meta.env`, `*.css`, `*?worker`) + the `*.vue`/`*.bbnf?raw`
    // ambient module declarations. The pre-split unified program included it via
    // `src/`; the demo graph needs it for the value.js `src/` modules it pulls in
    // through `@src/*` and for its own Vite-specific imports.
    "include": ["demo/", "src/vite-env.d.ts"]
}
